WEBVTT

00:01.460 --> 00:03.336
<i>- Previously on
"Superman and Lois"...</i>

00:03.337 --> 00:04.921
<i>- The night that
that thing came,</i>

00:04.922 --> 00:08.425
<i>I saw what happened
to your dad.</i>

00:08.426 --> 00:09.759
- Denise.
- No, it's OK.

00:09.760 --> 00:10.760
I'm not gonna,
like, say anything.

00:10.761 --> 00:12.178
- I don't feel strong.

00:12.179 --> 00:14.264
<i>- Well, for starters,
you died, so you</i>

00:14.265 --> 00:17.600
<i>can't expect to just bounce
back and be the same person.</i>

00:17.601 --> 00:19.769
Elizabeth Luthor.
If you could just talk to him.

00:19.770 --> 00:22.188
You are the one person
in the world he cares about.

00:22.189 --> 00:25.567
<i>- Lois Lane took 17
years of my life.</i>

00:25.568 --> 00:27.277
- Which you could
never get back.

00:27.278 --> 00:29.112
- There has to be a price.

00:29.113 --> 00:31.865
- I won't expose my son
to this kind of hatred,

00:31.866 --> 00:34.951
so stay out of my life forever.

00:34.952 --> 00:36.036
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:38.038 --> 00:44.878
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:44.879 --> 00:47.130
- [screams]

00:47.131 --> 00:54.221
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:33.135 --> 01:35.846
- Lex, is everything OK?

01:41.060 --> 01:42.644
Did something happen
with Elizabeth?

01:42.645 --> 01:45.272
- Where are we with the land?

01:47.107 --> 01:49.484
- I'm showing it to Bash
and the others this morning.

01:49.485 --> 01:52.362
They're less than enthusiastic
about moving headquarters.

01:52.363 --> 01:54.113
- They'll get over it.

01:54.114 --> 01:58.159
- Maybe, although some of their
concerns are understandable.

01:58.160 --> 02:01.162
<i>[tense music]</i>

02:01.163 --> 02:03.998
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:03.999 --> 02:05.708
Fine.

02:05.709 --> 02:08.795
But we still need to work
through the zoning issues.

02:08.796 --> 02:10.713
- You've spoken to Mayor Lang?

02:10.714 --> 02:12.215
- I'm pretty sure
she's the issue.

02:12.216 --> 02:14.384
There have been
roadblocks at every step.

02:14.385 --> 02:17.054
- I'll deal with her.

02:18.222 --> 02:19.472
Send this to Milton.

02:19.473 --> 02:22.725
Tell him I want
it by end of day.

02:22.726 --> 02:26.104
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:26.105 --> 02:27.230
- What are they for?

02:27.231 --> 02:29.482
- He'll know.

02:29.483 --> 02:31.401
- But I don't need to?

02:31.402 --> 02:35.154
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:35.155 --> 02:36.239
Fine.

02:36.240 --> 02:37.574
I'll get this to Milton.

02:37.575 --> 02:40.952
- Amanda.

02:40.953 --> 02:43.913
Wanting to be back
in my daughter's life

02:43.914 --> 02:48.585
was one of the things that
got me through prison.

02:48.586 --> 02:52.130
Your loyalty was the other.

02:52.131 --> 02:54.257
Make no mistake.

02:54.258 --> 02:56.759
I have a plan.

02:56.760 --> 02:58.553
I know exactly
how this will end.

02:58.554 --> 03:05.853
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:24.538 --> 03:27.457
<i>[light music]</i>

03:27.458 --> 03:34.798
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:38.052 --> 03:39.969
- We got everything on Luthor?

03:39.970 --> 03:42.639
- DOD surveillance files,
plus everything we dug up while

03:42.640 --> 03:44.390
we were at "The Daily Planet."

03:44.391 --> 03:45.725
- Let's get to work.

03:45.726 --> 03:46.809
I wanna send
Luthor back to prison

03:46.810 --> 03:48.311
before he has time to regroup.

03:48.312 --> 03:50.313
We're heading to "The Gazette."
- Good luck.

03:50.314 --> 03:51.898
- Hey, is that Jon?

03:51.899 --> 03:53.274
- Yeah. Three hours ago.

03:53.275 --> 03:55.319
Check this out.

03:56.904 --> 03:58.488
- That was all this morning?

03:58.489 --> 04:01.158
- Ask him yourself.

04:02.576 --> 04:05.370
- Your brother was just showing
us what you've been up to.

04:05.371 --> 04:07.038
- Oh, yeah. Couldn't sleep.

04:07.039 --> 04:09.165
Heard those screams in Chicago.

04:09.166 --> 04:10.875
We're out of eggs?

04:10.876 --> 04:12.627
- How many saves
have you made today?

04:12.628 --> 04:13.753
- Uh, three or four.

04:13.754 --> 04:15.046
Nothing too crazy.

04:15.047 --> 04:16.673
Wanna grab a bite
at Vicky May's?

04:16.674 --> 04:18.842
- Yeah, sure.
- Race ya.

04:20.719 --> 04:23.388
- That is starting to get old.

04:23.389 --> 04:24.806
- Jon's doing too much.

04:24.807 --> 04:26.683
He needs to slow down.

04:26.684 --> 04:27.684
- I'll talk to him.

04:27.685 --> 04:29.310
- Thanks, sweetie.

04:29.311 --> 04:30.979
- Hey, even though we support
you taking a step back

04:30.980 --> 04:32.855
from the superhero stuff,
it doesn't mean

04:32.856 --> 04:34.148
you can stay at the house
playing video games all day.

04:34.149 --> 04:35.858
- Maybe Vicky May's is hiring.

04:35.859 --> 04:37.945
Might be fun
working with Sarah.

04:40.072 --> 04:41.864
- He's right.
That is getting old.

04:41.865 --> 04:43.741
- Let's go, slow poke.

04:43.742 --> 04:49.872
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:49.873 --> 04:51.624
- What time did you
get home last night?

04:51.625 --> 04:53.960
- Uh, later than I planned.

04:53.961 --> 04:56.254
- You know you don't
have to come home.

04:56.255 --> 04:58.715
- I'm not leaving
you here alone.

04:58.716 --> 05:00.717
- Why?
Soph's with Dad all week.

05:00.718 --> 05:02.760
- John Henry has already
left for Metropolis,

05:02.761 --> 05:04.804
so it's not an issue.

05:04.805 --> 05:07.390
- Sucks he's barely
here these days.

05:07.391 --> 05:08.641
- Yeah.

05:08.642 --> 05:11.019
But we're trying
to figure it out.

05:11.020 --> 05:13.855
- Well, at least you have
something to look forward to.

05:13.856 --> 05:17.692
All I ever do is work
and sleep and work.

05:17.693 --> 05:19.736
- At least you're
making money, right?

05:19.737 --> 05:22.697
- Yeah.

05:22.698 --> 05:24.824
- Hey.

05:24.825 --> 05:28.828
Tonight, you and
me, girls night.

05:28.829 --> 05:30.872
- Deal.

05:30.873 --> 05:33.041
You know, I'm really glad
that you and Mr. Irons

05:33.042 --> 05:34.459
are spending time together.

05:34.460 --> 05:36.586
After everything with Dad,
you deserve it.

05:36.587 --> 05:37.837
- Thanks, sweetie.

05:37.838 --> 05:39.088
- You're welcome.

05:39.089 --> 05:42.550
Now I'm off to the
job that I hate.

05:42.551 --> 05:43.760
I love you.

05:43.761 --> 05:45.636
- Love you.

05:45.637 --> 05:47.556
[phone buzzes]

05:53.979 --> 05:55.271
- Otis Grisham.

05:55.272 --> 05:56.814
Rumor is Luthor got
him early release,

05:56.815 --> 05:58.399
so he's never gonna flip.

05:58.400 --> 06:01.611
- Yeah, and this bozo lawyered
up the second John Henry

06:01.612 --> 06:03.279
dropped him off at the DOD.

06:03.280 --> 06:05.907
We may have a shot with
Cheryl Kimble, though.

06:05.908 --> 06:08.911
- So we just need her to
come out of hiding again.

06:11.872 --> 06:14.165
What?
- Nothing.

06:14.166 --> 06:16.542
It's just, you've got some
salt and pepper going on.

06:16.543 --> 06:17.794
- What? Where?

06:17.795 --> 06:19.796
- I mean, there's a patch.

06:19.797 --> 06:20.922
- A patch?

06:20.923 --> 06:22.465
- It's just a little gray.

06:22.466 --> 06:25.259
You look handsome.

06:25.260 --> 06:27.221
There she is.

06:29.223 --> 06:30.640
- Is that Luthor's assistant?

06:30.641 --> 06:33.434
- As far as I can tell,
she doesn't have a title.

06:33.435 --> 06:35.937
One of the many things
I wanna ask her about.

06:35.938 --> 06:37.355
- You want me to come along?
- No.

06:37.356 --> 06:38.898
I can handle
Miss Business Suit.

06:38.899 --> 06:43.778
You look into
Cheryl Kimble for me.

06:43.779 --> 06:46.364
Stop worrying about your hair.

06:46.365 --> 06:48.575
- I'm not.

06:52.579 --> 06:53.830
- Hey.

06:53.831 --> 06:56.749
- He has been in there
for half an hour,

06:56.750 --> 06:59.585
and it is creeping me out.

06:59.586 --> 07:01.045
- What does he want?

07:01.046 --> 07:04.423
- He said he only
wants to talk to you.

07:04.424 --> 07:06.008
- Well, did you
tell him he needs

07:06.009 --> 07:07.677
to schedule an appointment?

07:07.678 --> 07:10.889
- I tried, but he just marched
straight into your office.

07:13.183 --> 07:15.935
- Sorry you've been waiting,
but unfortunately, we're

07:15.936 --> 07:17.645
gonna need to reschedule.

07:17.646 --> 07:19.648
- This will only take a minute.

07:22.109 --> 07:24.193
- What can I do for you?

07:24.194 --> 07:26.863
- More what you can stop doing.

07:26.864 --> 07:28.197
- I'm not following.

07:28.198 --> 07:30.408
- These zoning
restrictions of yours.

07:30.409 --> 07:32.368
They're interfering
with my plans.

07:32.369 --> 07:34.078
- There's a lot
of red tape, I know,

07:34.079 --> 07:35.997
but that's just how things
are done around here.

07:35.998 --> 07:37.290
- Not anymore.

07:37.291 --> 07:38.624
- Excuse me?

07:38.625 --> 07:40.835
I'm building my new
headquarters in Smallville.

07:40.836 --> 07:43.213
Nothing you do is
going to change that.

07:45.632 --> 07:46.716
- Is that a threat?

07:46.717 --> 07:48.217
- Just a fact.

07:48.218 --> 07:49.719
- I think we're done here.

07:49.720 --> 07:51.137
- Do your job, Mayor Lang.

07:51.138 --> 07:53.556
- My job is protecting
the people of Smallville

07:53.557 --> 07:54.724
from someone like you.

07:54.725 --> 07:56.017
- I'll only ask once.

07:56.018 --> 07:57.852
- You already have my answer.

07:57.853 --> 08:00.855
<i>[tense music]</i>

08:00.856 --> 08:05.193
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:05.194 --> 08:09.113
- This security system
of yours, it's just like one

08:09.114 --> 08:11.949
an old acquaintance
of mine built.

08:11.950 --> 08:15.912
When his time came,

08:15.913 --> 08:18.624
it didn't do much
to protect him.

08:20.167 --> 08:23.794
- Get out of my office
and don't come back.

08:23.795 --> 08:31.136
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:44.691 --> 08:45.942
- What the hell is
Luthor thinking?

08:45.943 --> 08:47.985
- He believes this will
be the perfect location

08:47.986 --> 08:49.570
for our next headquarters.

08:49.571 --> 08:51.530
- Yeah, maybe if we're
in the fertilizer business.

08:51.531 --> 08:53.699
- The land is cheap
and undeveloped.

08:53.700 --> 08:55.534
- For good reason.

08:55.535 --> 08:58.204
Amanda, there is no
way I can support

08:58.205 --> 08:59.789
this in good conscience.

08:59.790 --> 09:03.793
- This is what Lex wants,
so you better get on board.

09:03.794 --> 09:08.839
- Look, the rest of us don't
have whatever cozy relationship

09:08.840 --> 09:11.008
it is you have with Luthor.

09:11.009 --> 09:13.344
We need to know why
he's doing this.

09:13.345 --> 09:14.887
- It's simple.

09:14.888 --> 09:18.808
Luthor's moving here
to harass my family.

09:18.809 --> 09:20.059
- What's she talking about?

09:20.060 --> 09:21.352
- Leave.

09:21.353 --> 09:23.729
I'll handle her.
- Go ahead, tell him.

09:23.730 --> 09:25.147
- I said leave.

09:25.148 --> 09:27.984
<i>[tense music]</i>

09:27.985 --> 09:31.237
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:31.238 --> 09:33.489
So prison wasn't enough,
and now you're trying

09:33.490 --> 09:35.199
to sabotage his business?

09:35.200 --> 09:37.034
- Everything I said was true,
and you know it.

09:37.035 --> 09:38.661
- This is a business decision.

09:38.662 --> 09:41.163
Anything else is just
more fake news from you.

09:41.164 --> 09:44.875
- What exactly is it
you do for Luthor?

09:44.876 --> 09:46.210
- Is that why you're here,

09:46.211 --> 09:48.713
to ask about my job
responsibilities?

09:48.714 --> 09:52.508
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:52.509 --> 09:58.055
- You have no idea
how dangerous he is.

09:58.056 --> 09:59.557
He killed my father.

09:59.558 --> 10:01.809
- I thought it was that
big, scary monster.

10:01.810 --> 10:05.021
Next, you'll probably say
he killed Superman, too.

10:05.022 --> 10:07.691
Or maybe even your husband.

10:10.068 --> 10:11.527
You can't beat him.

10:11.528 --> 10:13.529
- You know, with that
big, scary monster gone,

10:13.530 --> 10:15.072
I'm starting
to like my chances.

10:15.073 --> 10:16.449
- Doesn't matter.

10:16.450 --> 10:18.200
Whatever Lex sets
his mind to gets done.

10:18.201 --> 10:21.329
- Not when it comes
to his daughter.

10:21.330 --> 10:23.289
Oh, he didn't tell you.

10:23.290 --> 10:26.959
Elizabeth came here and asked
him to be a part of her life,

10:26.960 --> 10:31.756
but he couldn't walk away
from his obsession with me.

10:31.757 --> 10:34.258
Luthor is losing control,
and if you're not careful,

10:34.259 --> 10:35.926
he'll take you down with him.

10:35.927 --> 10:37.386
- That'll never happen.

10:37.387 --> 10:40.222
- The only person
he cares about is himself.

10:40.223 --> 10:41.640
If you don't believe me,
look at how

10:41.641 --> 10:44.477
he treated his own daughter.

10:44.478 --> 10:46.187
The real question is,
what happens when

10:46.188 --> 10:49.023
you two don't see eye to eye?

10:49.024 --> 10:52.026
<i>[tense music]</i>

10:52.027 --> 10:57.824
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:00.952 --> 11:03.997
[scanner beeping]

11:16.134 --> 11:17.510
- Everything OK?

11:17.511 --> 11:18.511
- Yeah, of course.

11:18.512 --> 11:20.012
Why wouldn't it be?

11:20.013 --> 11:22.431
That will be $19.38.

11:22.432 --> 11:24.600
- OK. Ah, keep the change.

11:24.601 --> 11:26.268
- OK.

11:26.269 --> 11:27.269
- Hey, Clark.

11:27.270 --> 11:28.270
- Hey, hey.

11:28.271 --> 11:29.313
How's it--

11:29.314 --> 11:31.315
- Um, hey.

11:31.316 --> 11:32.817
Uh, that's new.

11:32.818 --> 11:34.026
Is everything all right?

11:34.027 --> 11:35.277
- Yeah, no, of course.

11:35.278 --> 11:37.279
Why wouldn't it be?
- Yeah, no.

11:37.280 --> 11:40.616
Denise, do you mind
getting my package?

11:40.617 --> 11:43.285
- Yes, of course.
- Thank you.

11:43.286 --> 11:46.288
So, Lex Luthor just
came by my office

11:46.289 --> 11:50.084
trying to intimidate me into
signing off on his land deal.

11:50.085 --> 11:51.961
- Lana, you have to
be careful with him.

11:51.962 --> 11:52.962
- I know.

11:52.963 --> 11:54.630
Lois already warned me.

11:54.631 --> 11:57.925
But I'm not gonna just let
him build his new headquarters

11:57.926 --> 11:59.135
in Smallville.

11:59.136 --> 12:00.719
- Wait, new headquarters?
Where?

12:00.720 --> 12:03.389
- Aidy Manning's place,
up off of Highway 40.

12:03.390 --> 12:04.974
- I didn't know it
was on the market.

12:04.975 --> 12:07.393
- It wasn't until he
made an offer for five

12:07.394 --> 12:09.019
times what it's worth.

12:09.020 --> 12:13.357
I'm headed to Aidy's now to
try to talk her out of it.

12:13.358 --> 12:14.900
You should come with me.

12:14.901 --> 12:17.278
- I mean, I don't know how
much help that would be.

12:17.279 --> 12:20.239
- Clark, your mom
was a guardian

12:20.240 --> 12:22.408
angel around these parts.

12:22.409 --> 12:24.869
Hearing from you
would mean a lot.

12:24.870 --> 12:25.911
- Yeah, sure.

12:25.912 --> 12:27.914
Anything to help.

12:31.334 --> 12:35.337
- So, did you forget how to eat
food like a normal human being?

12:35.338 --> 12:36.839
- You know you can
breathe, right?

12:36.840 --> 12:38.340
- I just skipped
out on breakfast.

12:38.341 --> 12:39.842
- Why?
Where were you?

12:39.843 --> 12:40.759
- Oh.

12:40.760 --> 12:43.679
Toronto, San Juan, Gastonia.

12:43.680 --> 12:45.598
Superboy here has
been really busy.

12:45.599 --> 12:47.641
- Right.
It's better than serving eggs.

12:47.642 --> 12:49.602
- That's cause you've
never been to Gastonia.

12:49.603 --> 12:51.312
- Jon, most people
in Smallville

12:51.313 --> 12:54.231
have never been anywhere but
here, so count yourself lucky.

12:54.232 --> 12:57.526
- Hey!
Well, well, well.

12:57.527 --> 13:01.238
Now, if it isn't my two
favorite student athletes.

13:01.239 --> 13:03.699
Move over, Shortstack.

13:03.700 --> 13:05.952
Come on.

13:08.497 --> 13:11.040
You boys ready for
the football season?

13:11.041 --> 13:13.918
- Coach, I'm kind of
banned from the team.

13:13.919 --> 13:17.213
- I haven't played
in two years.

13:17.214 --> 13:18.797
- Let me worry about that.

13:18.798 --> 13:21.300
How about you two just
keep worrying about being--

13:21.301 --> 13:23.595
[whispering]
Super?

13:24.554 --> 13:25.888
- Coach, I don't think that's--

13:25.889 --> 13:29.642
- Way I see it, we got
a real opportunity here.

13:29.643 --> 13:32.686
Why not take advantage of it?

13:32.687 --> 13:34.396
- I mean, there's
so many reasons.

13:34.397 --> 13:36.023
- Think of the possibilities.

13:36.024 --> 13:41.403
State titles,
scholarships, girls.

13:41.404 --> 13:42.905
See.

13:42.906 --> 13:45.617
Your brother knows
what I'm talking about.

13:47.577 --> 13:51.205
- Ah, listen,
coach, I got to run.

13:51.206 --> 13:52.581
- Hey, so that's a yes, right?

13:52.582 --> 13:54.834
- Definitely not.

13:56.253 --> 13:58.254
- What about you, Curlicue?

13:58.255 --> 14:01.674
- I'm sorry to let you down,
but his lawyers have already

14:01.675 --> 14:03.259
drawn up the paperwork.

14:03.260 --> 14:05.761
I was just about to
head over to Manito's.

14:05.762 --> 14:09.014
- Lex Luthor is bad
for this town, Aidy.

14:09.015 --> 14:11.016
- Sure.
I've heard the rumors.

14:11.017 --> 14:13.102
But Luthor didn't
murder those people.

14:13.103 --> 14:14.812
Even Lois said so.

14:14.813 --> 14:17.147
- Which doesn't make
him a good person.

14:17.148 --> 14:20.609
We can't let someone
like that into this town.

14:20.610 --> 14:23.153
Not after what happened
with Morgan Edge.

14:23.154 --> 14:28.117
- It's just, I'll never have
an opportunity like this again.

14:28.118 --> 14:29.660
- I know.

14:29.661 --> 14:34.207
And we wouldn't be here
if this wasn't serious.

14:35.709 --> 14:37.961
- Is Luthor really that bad?

14:39.921 --> 14:41.797
- Yeah.

14:41.798 --> 14:43.882
Yeah, he really is.

14:43.883 --> 14:46.385
Like, I know it's a lot
of money to turn down.

14:46.386 --> 14:52.600
- I mean, it's nothing compared
to what you sacrificed.

14:52.601 --> 14:54.018
- I'm sorry?

14:54.019 --> 14:56.145
- Everything you've
done for this town.

14:56.146 --> 15:01.525
For the-- just wouldn't feel
right cashing in if you're

15:01.526 --> 15:02.985
that worried about it.

15:02.986 --> 15:06.030
- Uh, Aidy, I'm not
really sure what you--

15:06.031 --> 15:10.117
- Let me get my sweater and
I'll ride into town with you.

15:10.118 --> 15:12.453
Talk to his lawyers.

15:12.454 --> 15:15.456
<i>[soft music]</i>

15:15.457 --> 15:17.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:17.042 --> 15:19.293
- Is it just me,
or did it feel like Aidy

15:19.294 --> 15:21.087
knows who I really am?

15:26.217 --> 15:29.136
<i>[tense music]</i>

15:29.137 --> 15:36.269
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:39.648 --> 15:41.523
- You are not
gonna believe this.

15:41.524 --> 15:44.985
Luthor is moving
Luthor Corp to Smallville.

15:44.986 --> 15:47.404
- Not gonna happen anymore.

15:47.405 --> 15:48.864
- How do you know that?

15:48.865 --> 15:51.241
- I ran into Lana
at Brit & Dunn's earlier,

15:51.242 --> 15:53.661
and she asked me to go
to Aidy Manning's to help

15:53.662 --> 15:54.870
convince her not to sell.

15:54.871 --> 15:56.288
- And it worked?

15:56.289 --> 15:57.790
- They're going to
talk to his lawyers

15:57.791 --> 15:58.874
right now to tell
him the deal's off.

15:58.875 --> 16:00.334
- How did you convince her?

16:00.335 --> 16:02.711
- Well, that part was
pretty easy, considering

16:02.712 --> 16:04.380
she thinks I'm Superman.

16:04.381 --> 16:05.798
- What?

16:05.799 --> 16:07.967
- Yeah, and I'm pretty sure
she's not the only one.

16:09.803 --> 16:10.844
- How do you feel about that?

16:10.845 --> 16:13.181
- Uh--

16:14.933 --> 16:18.269
- Got these for you guys.

16:19.145 --> 16:20.396
- Where have you been?

16:20.397 --> 16:22.731
- Putting out
my second fire in a row.

16:22.732 --> 16:25.109
Then made a few more saves.

16:25.110 --> 16:27.570
Last one was in Montreal.

16:32.450 --> 16:34.702
Heard they had great bagels,
so...

16:34.703 --> 16:36.620
- Have a seat.

16:36.621 --> 16:38.497
- Oh.

16:38.498 --> 16:41.500
What did I do wrong?

16:41.501 --> 16:42.626
- You wanna work here?

16:42.627 --> 16:45.087
- Just until school
starts back up.

16:45.088 --> 16:46.964
- Well, we don't have anything.

16:46.965 --> 16:48.424
- Sarah.

16:48.425 --> 16:50.300
What do you mean?

16:50.301 --> 16:52.428
- Have you asked Denise
at Brit & Dunn's?

16:52.429 --> 16:53.429
- Yes, I did.

16:53.430 --> 16:54.888
And she said ever
since Jon quit,

16:54.889 --> 16:56.223
she had to cover
all of his shifts,

16:56.224 --> 16:57.850
and now she has
a strict no Kent policy.

16:57.851 --> 16:59.143
- Yeah.

16:59.144 --> 17:01.019
- Look, Sarah,
please, I need this.

17:01.020 --> 17:04.648
- Yeah, and I need to not share
shifts with my ex-boyfriend.

17:04.649 --> 17:05.774
- Come on.

17:05.775 --> 17:07.109
This isn't really about us.

17:07.110 --> 17:08.610
- What is wrong with you?

17:08.611 --> 17:10.529
I know you're taking
time off from being

17:10.530 --> 17:13.490
a superhero and everything,
but you can fly.

17:13.491 --> 17:14.616
- So?

17:14.617 --> 17:16.910
- So you can go anywhere
and do anything.

17:16.911 --> 17:19.455
I mean, do you really think
I like taking orders all day?

17:19.456 --> 17:22.624
No, but I messed up,
and I'm making up for it.

17:22.625 --> 17:24.460
But you, you could be
having so much fun.

17:24.461 --> 17:27.254
You can go anywhere in the
world and find a summer job.

17:27.255 --> 17:29.173
- It doesn't work like that.

17:29.174 --> 17:31.133
- Do you know what I would
give to have your freedom,

17:31.134 --> 17:34.094
to go someplace new?

17:34.095 --> 17:36.138
- Sarah, you don't
need powers to do that.

17:36.139 --> 17:39.141
<i>[soft music]</i>

17:39.142 --> 17:41.769
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:41.770 --> 17:44.313
Look, Sarah, will you
please just reconsider?

17:44.314 --> 17:46.231
- Not happening.
- Please.

17:46.232 --> 17:49.569
- Hey, Mr. Taylor.
Have a seat.

17:52.906 --> 17:54.281
- You're walking away?

17:54.282 --> 17:56.909
- It's not like she
actually signed anything.

17:56.910 --> 17:58.327
Aidy was simply considering--

17:58.328 --> 18:01.289
- You agreed to the
terms, Ms. Manning.

18:02.916 --> 18:05.334
We had a handshake deal.

18:05.335 --> 18:06.585
- I know.

18:06.586 --> 18:09.171
And I'm sorry.

18:09.172 --> 18:11.298
But I've had a change of heart.

18:11.299 --> 18:17.137
- Then please, give me
a chance to change it back.

18:17.138 --> 18:20.099
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:20.850 --> 18:22.726
- You're asking me to do less.

18:22.727 --> 18:25.354
- We're asking you
to strike a balance.

18:25.355 --> 18:28.315
- You can barely hear anymore,
and you have Lex Luthor

18:28.316 --> 18:29.608
breathing down your neck.

18:29.609 --> 18:31.151
- Look, you've
been very helpful.

18:31.152 --> 18:32.444
But when you push
yourself too hard,

18:32.445 --> 18:34.363
that's when
mistakes can happen.

18:34.364 --> 18:37.032
- I won't take
no for an answer, Aidy.

18:37.033 --> 18:38.367
- You're gonna have to.

18:38.368 --> 18:41.412
- Miss Lang's
arguing with Luthor.

18:44.290 --> 18:45.332
- This doesn't involve you.

18:45.333 --> 18:46.625
- She said the deal is off.

18:46.626 --> 18:47.876
- Tell me what you need.

18:47.877 --> 18:49.545
- She needs you to stop.
- What's your number?

18:49.546 --> 18:50.712
- I said enough.

18:50.713 --> 18:54.132
- Stay the hell
out of my business!

18:54.133 --> 18:57.052
- Then leave her alone.

18:57.053 --> 18:59.305
- Lana?

19:00.974 --> 19:02.224
- It's OK, Clark.

19:02.225 --> 19:04.477
Mr. Luthor was just leaving.

19:12.193 --> 19:14.736
- 10 million.

19:14.737 --> 19:18.157
Sell me your farm,
you get $10 million.

19:20.285 --> 19:22.662
And so will everyone
else in this bar.

19:27.834 --> 19:30.128
Do we have a deal?

19:35.967 --> 19:39.011
- It doesn't feel right, Aidy.

19:39.012 --> 19:41.388
- He wants it this bad.

19:41.389 --> 19:43.515
Something's wrong.

19:43.516 --> 19:46.518
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:46.519 --> 19:50.355
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:50.356 --> 19:52.733
- The answer is still no.

19:52.734 --> 19:56.612
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:56.613 --> 19:59.072
- Like I said,

19:59.073 --> 20:01.617
you were just leaving.

20:01.618 --> 20:08.917
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:40.031 --> 20:41.698
- What the hell were
you thinking back there?

20:41.699 --> 20:43.075
That was so far
past acceptable.

20:43.076 --> 20:44.493
- She should have
never had a chance

20:44.494 --> 20:45.535
to walk away from the deal.

20:45.536 --> 20:47.162
- This isn't prison, Lex.

20:47.163 --> 20:48.872
You can't just bully everyone
into doing what you want.

20:48.873 --> 20:50.666
- Tell Milton to send
his installation team.

20:50.667 --> 20:53.085
- Do you even know what it is
that you're doing here anymore?

20:53.086 --> 20:55.545
Because you're not the only
one who can see 10 steps ahead,

20:55.546 --> 20:59.091
and I am telling you that
all this, it's a bad move.

20:59.092 --> 21:02.469
- I told you, everything
is under control.

21:02.470 --> 21:03.720
- Really?

21:03.721 --> 21:05.347
Because it sounds
like your daughter

21:05.348 --> 21:06.765
wanted to be in your life,
but you just couldn't walk

21:06.766 --> 21:09.435
away from revenge summer camp.

21:10.853 --> 21:12.854
You didn't think that was
something I should know?

21:12.855 --> 21:14.356
- It wasn't the time.

21:14.357 --> 21:18.360
- How dare you keep
me in the dark.

21:18.361 --> 21:20.904
After running your business
for the last 10 years.

21:20.905 --> 21:22.447
- And making millions.

21:22.448 --> 21:24.199
- Which I earned.

21:24.200 --> 21:25.742
Every damn penny.

21:25.743 --> 21:28.370
And now you're threatening the
future that I built for us.

21:28.371 --> 21:31.373
<i>[tense music]</i>

21:31.374 --> 21:35.627
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:35.628 --> 21:40.048
- Do you still believe in me?

21:40.049 --> 21:41.717
Amanda?

21:41.718 --> 21:43.635
- I don't know.

21:43.636 --> 21:50.977
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:53.563 --> 21:55.939
- Then figure it out.

21:55.940 --> 21:59.317
Because you have to choose.

21:59.318 --> 22:03.947
Me or them.

22:03.948 --> 22:06.450
There is no middle ground.

22:06.451 --> 22:13.791
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:18.337 --> 22:19.713
- It's about time
that somebody stood

22:19.714 --> 22:22.090
up to that bald headed loser.

22:22.091 --> 22:24.885
- Aidy is the real hero.

22:24.886 --> 22:28.180
She turned down a fortune.

22:28.181 --> 22:29.598
- Do you think
that he's gonna try

22:29.599 --> 22:31.767
and buy somebody else's land?

22:31.768 --> 22:33.226
- No.

22:33.227 --> 22:35.771
Not after the way
they stood up to him.

22:35.772 --> 22:39.274
I mean, you should
have seen it, Sarah.

22:39.275 --> 22:43.863
I have never been more
proud of Smallville.

22:46.324 --> 22:50.285
- So there's something that
I wanna talk to you about.

22:50.286 --> 22:55.165
But before you make up your
mind, just hear me out.

22:55.166 --> 22:57.084
- OK.

22:57.085 --> 22:59.961
- I wanna study
abroad next year.

22:59.962 --> 23:02.130
- Like, out of the
country abroad?

23:02.131 --> 23:06.093
- Yeah, I could learn a new
language and meet new people.

23:06.094 --> 23:08.678
- You don't have to travel
thousands of miles away

23:08.679 --> 23:09.846
to meet new people.

23:09.847 --> 23:10.972
- Well, it would
look really good

23:10.973 --> 23:12.641
on my college applications.

23:12.642 --> 23:16.019
- So would playing sports or
joining an after school club.

23:16.020 --> 23:17.479
- Mom, I'm serious.

23:17.480 --> 23:19.524
I think this would be
really good for me.

23:23.152 --> 23:26.321
- These programs
cost a lot of money.

23:26.322 --> 23:27.489
- What if I help?

23:27.490 --> 23:31.243
I could get a
scholarship or something.

23:31.244 --> 23:34.663
- Where is this
even coming from?

23:34.664 --> 23:37.707
- I just feel like ever
since I crashed my car,

23:37.708 --> 23:42.003
I've been trying to take baby
steps to find my right path.

23:42.004 --> 23:48.553
But I need something bigger and
I need something life changing.

23:51.097 --> 23:53.306
- I just don't know
that I'm ready to have

23:53.307 --> 23:56.059
you be gone for a whole year.

23:56.060 --> 23:57.477
You're only 16.

23:57.478 --> 23:59.146
- I could FaceTime
you every single day,

23:59.147 --> 24:00.480
and I could write you letters.

24:00.481 --> 24:03.024
I mean, who even
writes letters anymore?

24:03.025 --> 24:06.027
<i>[soft music]</i>

24:06.028 --> 24:12.701
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:12.702 --> 24:15.204
- Where would you even go?

24:19.292 --> 24:21.418
- Yo. Were you at the fortress?

24:21.419 --> 24:24.045
- Yeah, I just wanted
to get in some training.

24:24.046 --> 24:26.464
Sorry to leave you
with Gaines before.

24:26.465 --> 24:27.716
How'd that go?

24:27.717 --> 24:30.135
- Dude, the guy will not
take no for an answer.

24:30.136 --> 24:32.262
He made me promise to
watch all of <i>Varsity Blues</i>

24:32.263 --> 24:34.139
before giving him
a final decision.

24:34.140 --> 24:36.308
- What?
That James Van Der Beek movie?

24:36.309 --> 24:39.644
- Yes. And it was awesome.

24:39.645 --> 24:42.314
And he may have a point.

24:42.315 --> 24:44.858
But look, do you
think that maybe

24:44.859 --> 24:47.444
you're just going a little too
all-in on the Superboy thing?

24:47.445 --> 24:49.112
- Wow.

24:49.113 --> 24:50.947
You've been talking
to Mom and Dad.

24:50.948 --> 24:53.241
- No, I just mean, like--

24:53.242 --> 24:55.076
bro, you've been doing a lot.

24:55.077 --> 24:57.329
- So what, you're gonna give
me superhero advice now?

24:57.330 --> 25:00.582
- No, I just mean that maybe
you should slow down a little.

25:00.583 --> 25:02.083
- You know I wouldn't
have to do so

25:02.084 --> 25:04.586
much if you were helping me.

25:04.587 --> 25:06.171
But you're the one
choosing to work at a diner

25:06.172 --> 25:09.424
instead of saving
people's lives.

25:09.425 --> 25:13.470
- That's because when I get
involved, I make things worse.

25:13.471 --> 25:15.473
- Jordan.

25:18.517 --> 25:22.103
- Ah, by the way, I didn't
get the job at the diner.

25:22.104 --> 25:25.441
I guess Sarah agrees with you.

25:28.152 --> 25:29.861
- Can you believe
John Henry and Lana

25:29.862 --> 25:31.363
have been dating for a month?

25:31.364 --> 25:33.741
- I know, I'm really
happy for them.

25:36.035 --> 25:37.994
- Oh, Clark.
- What?

25:37.995 --> 25:39.162
- Is that what
you've been doing

25:39.163 --> 25:41.665
in there, dyeing your hair?

25:41.666 --> 25:43.124
- Just a little.

25:43.125 --> 25:44.501
- Yeah, I can smell it
all the way over here.

25:44.502 --> 25:46.294
- Oh, come on.
It's not that bad.

25:46.295 --> 25:47.796
- You don't need to hide it.

25:47.797 --> 25:49.214
I like the salt and pepper.

25:49.215 --> 25:50.590
- Yeah, I know.

25:50.591 --> 25:51.883
It's just, I don't
think now's the time

25:51.884 --> 25:54.678
for Superman to be going gray.

25:54.679 --> 25:57.556
People are still worried after
everything that's happened.

26:00.101 --> 26:02.520
- You sure that's
what this is about?

26:04.230 --> 26:05.647
- It's not just the gray.

26:05.648 --> 26:08.775
It's me not being as strong.

26:08.776 --> 26:11.654
Uh, my hearing.

26:12.822 --> 26:15.991
I just didn't think
I was gonna get old,

26:15.992 --> 26:17.200
at least not anytime soon.

26:17.201 --> 26:19.786
- You're not old, you're older.

26:19.787 --> 26:20.954
There's a difference.

26:20.955 --> 26:22.998
- Yeah, but I'm not what I was.

26:22.999 --> 26:25.376
- Welcome to being human.

26:27.420 --> 26:30.171
- I think part of me always
wanted to not be so different,

26:30.172 --> 26:34.592
but I guess I just
didn't expect--

26:34.593 --> 26:36.845
- All the baggage?

26:36.846 --> 26:40.140
Getting older isn't all bad.

26:40.141 --> 26:44.311
And at least now we can
age gracefully together.

26:44.312 --> 26:45.687
- Yeah, that'd be worth it.

26:45.688 --> 26:48.398
- I hope so.

26:48.399 --> 26:49.816
Please wash that stuff
out of your hair.

26:49.817 --> 26:52.111
It reeks.
- Yeah.

26:55.281 --> 26:58.199
[thunder rumbling]

26:58.200 --> 27:05.541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:46.957 --> 27:50.169
- [coughing]

27:59.970 --> 28:02.889
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

28:02.890 --> 28:07.018
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:07.019 --> 28:08.603
[glass shattering]

28:08.604 --> 28:10.606
Sarah!

28:13.776 --> 28:15.903
[glass shattering]

28:21.200 --> 28:24.412
[grunting]

28:27.915 --> 28:30.875
- Should've minded
your own business.

28:30.876 --> 28:38.217
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:39.718 --> 28:41.761
- Mom!

28:41.762 --> 28:43.304
Mom, are you OK?

28:43.305 --> 28:45.599
- [panting]

28:51.897 --> 28:54.816
<i>[tense music]</i>

28:54.817 --> 29:01.614
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:01.615 --> 29:04.200
- All the windows are open.

29:04.201 --> 29:07.620
- Gas.

29:07.621 --> 29:10.623
- We're gonna go
check on Sarah.

29:10.624 --> 29:11.791
- Clark.

29:11.792 --> 29:13.961
Over here.

29:18.424 --> 29:20.842
- Otis Grisham.

29:20.843 --> 29:23.387
- Luthor must have sent him.

29:32.480 --> 29:35.690
- I woke up because
I smelled gas.

29:35.691 --> 29:39.569
I went into the kitchen
and saw that the security

29:39.570 --> 29:44.574
system wasn't working,
and that's when he attacked me.

29:44.575 --> 29:47.911
- His name is Otis Grisham.

29:47.912 --> 29:50.538
- He did time with Luthor.

29:50.539 --> 29:55.961
- So Lex Luthor tried to
kill me over a land deal?

29:58.297 --> 30:01.216
- Sweetie, can you
get Lana some water?

30:01.217 --> 30:03.302
- Yeah.

30:05.679 --> 30:06.888
- Lois.

30:06.889 --> 30:08.181
Sarah was here.

30:08.182 --> 30:10.391
- I know. I know.

30:10.392 --> 30:12.602
But you're both safe now.

30:12.603 --> 30:15.396
- It's just, if I
hadn't woken up--

30:15.397 --> 30:17.690
- I know how scary
this is, but they're

30:17.691 --> 30:20.109
taking Grisham to the DOD,
and I promise,

30:20.110 --> 30:22.570
I will make him talk.

30:22.571 --> 30:26.866
- He had his hands
around my neck,

30:26.867 --> 30:31.204
and he was just squeezing
harder and harder.

30:31.205 --> 30:33.373
I couldn't breathe.

30:33.374 --> 30:39.672
Just-- I thought
I was gonna die.

30:43.175 --> 30:44.884
<i>- You sure you're OK?</i>

30:44.885 --> 30:46.886
Your hands are shaking.

30:46.887 --> 30:48.555
- That's kind of what
happens when you watch

30:48.556 --> 30:50.223
your mom almost get murdered.

30:50.224 --> 30:52.934
Thank God my dad makes us
sleep with bats under our bed.

30:52.935 --> 30:55.938
It's the only thing
I had to protect us.

30:59.358 --> 31:00.441
I didn't mean it like that.

31:00.442 --> 31:02.735
- It's OK.
You're right.

31:02.736 --> 31:04.612
- We should have
been here, Sarah.

31:04.613 --> 31:06.489
- No, I don't blame you guys.

31:06.490 --> 31:07.949
It's not like you guys
are waiting around all day

31:07.950 --> 31:09.325
for something bad to happen.

31:09.326 --> 31:10.827
- No, but I should
have been listening.

31:10.828 --> 31:13.538
- I've been going so
hard lately, I didn't

31:13.539 --> 31:15.248
even hear your mom's scream.

31:15.249 --> 31:17.458
- It's OK.

31:17.459 --> 31:19.210
Seriously.

31:19.211 --> 31:21.004
- Sure.

31:21.005 --> 31:23.172
- OK.

31:23.173 --> 31:25.925
- I'm gonna go check on my mom.

31:25.926 --> 31:28.845
<i>[soft music]</i>

31:28.846 --> 31:33.266
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:33.267 --> 31:34.434
- Where's your father?

31:34.435 --> 31:36.894
- Isn't he with you?

31:36.895 --> 31:40.898
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:40.899 --> 31:42.609
- Luthor!

31:42.610 --> 31:45.904
[thunder rumbling]

31:48.282 --> 31:50.576
Luthor!

31:51.994 --> 31:53.328
Luthor!

31:53.329 --> 31:56.624
[thunder rumbling]

31:58.917 --> 32:00.918
Get out here!

32:00.919 --> 32:03.921
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:03.922 --> 32:11.055
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:21.440 --> 32:24.025
- You look upset.

32:24.026 --> 32:25.652
Did something happen?

32:25.653 --> 32:27.070
- We know it was you.

32:27.071 --> 32:28.655
- I don't follow.

32:28.656 --> 32:31.032
- You harass my family,
you kill my father-in-law,

32:31.033 --> 32:34.035
now you try to kill my friend
and her 16-year-old daughter.

32:34.036 --> 32:37.705
- Again with these
false accusations?

32:37.706 --> 32:40.333
You and your wife need to
stop trying to set me up.

32:40.334 --> 32:42.628
- Stop lying!

32:44.004 --> 32:48.716
Your friend Otis is in custody,
and we will make him talk.

32:48.717 --> 32:51.428
- We'll see about that.

32:54.223 --> 32:56.641
- This is over.

32:56.642 --> 32:59.728
We are going to end you.

33:02.648 --> 33:04.232
- You're going to end me?

33:04.233 --> 33:10.405
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:10.406 --> 33:13.909
Try doing it without powers.

33:15.869 --> 33:19.038
You have nothing on me!

33:19.039 --> 33:20.748
And you never will,

33:20.749 --> 33:24.752
even when there is nothing
left of your pathetic family!

33:24.753 --> 33:27.046
<i>- ♪ The tapping of the feet
seem loud ♪</i>

33:27.047 --> 33:30.758
<i>♪ There's a girl
in a whirlwind cloud ♪</i>

33:30.759 --> 33:34.971
<i>♪ I danced
with a Spaniard man ♪</i>

33:34.972 --> 33:40.518
<i>♪ Till we had no breath left
in our pounding chests ♪</i>

33:40.519 --> 33:43.938
<i>♪ I shudder like
I'm all bereft ♪</i>

33:43.939 --> 33:46.941
<i>♪ I danced grief
from my pores ♪</i>

33:46.942 --> 33:50.945
<i>♪ The beat pounds like
a knocking at the door ♪</i>

33:50.946 --> 33:54.157
<i>[IDLES'
"When the Lights Come On"]</i>

33:54.158 --> 33:56.451
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:56.452 --> 33:59.454
<i>[ringing]</i>

33:59.455 --> 34:06.795
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:11.800 --> 34:16.637
<i>♪ Recognize or recognizes me ♪</i>

34:16.638 --> 34:18.473
<i>♪ I black out ♪</i>

34:18.474 --> 34:21.476
<i>♪ I don't want your dim sum ♪</i>

34:21.477 --> 34:22.977
<i>♪ It's 3:00 a.m. ♪</i>

34:22.978 --> 34:25.563
<i>♪ I wanna dance
till the sun comes ♪</i>

34:25.564 --> 34:27.148
- No.

34:27.149 --> 34:29.066
The lights.

34:29.067 --> 34:32.320
<i>- ♪ I wanna tear through the
night like an angel flare ♪</i>

34:32.321 --> 34:34.280
<i>♪ I'm a 10-foot snare ♪</i>

34:34.281 --> 34:37.784
<i>♪ That cuts in the sky
with no care ♪</i>

34:37.785 --> 34:41.496
<i>♪ No care, no care, no ♪</i>

34:41.497 --> 34:47.168
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:47.169 --> 34:53.341
<i>♪ A narcissist
on a cucking stool ♪</i>

34:53.342 --> 34:54.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:54.718 --> 34:59.555
<i>♪ The kids are not... ♪</i>

34:59.556 --> 35:03.226
- [grunting]

35:03.227 --> 35:06.563
- [laughs]

35:07.689 --> 35:10.608
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

35:10.609 --> 35:17.950
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:19.660 --> 35:23.621
I always knew
Superman was a facade.

35:23.622 --> 35:27.626
Now they see who
you really are!

35:29.920 --> 35:31.504
- Leave!

35:31.505 --> 35:33.841
Don't ever come back.

35:36.718 --> 35:39.637
[thunder rumbling]

35:39.638 --> 35:46.979
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:52.150 --> 35:54.653
[device crunches]

35:59.575 --> 36:01.909
- Your face is still bruised.

36:01.910 --> 36:04.954
- Well, once the sun comes
out, it should start to heal.

36:04.955 --> 36:06.581
- Normally it would
have healed already.

36:06.582 --> 36:09.208
I think you need to go talk
to your mom about this.

36:09.209 --> 36:11.169
- It's fine.

36:12.921 --> 36:14.255
- That was awesome.

36:14.256 --> 36:15.590
- You went full
"Mortal Kombat" on him.

36:15.591 --> 36:17.091
- Clark Kent wins.

36:17.092 --> 36:18.175
- OK, OK.

36:18.176 --> 36:19.927
I don't think anybody
won tonight.

36:19.928 --> 36:22.096
- Pretty sure Luthor's
face says otherwise.

36:22.097 --> 36:24.640
- That's what he wanted,
for your father

36:24.641 --> 36:26.183
to stoop down to his level.

36:26.184 --> 36:28.311
- He had it coming.
He tried to kill Miss Lang.

36:28.312 --> 36:30.187
- If anyone deserved
to have their ass beat--

36:30.188 --> 36:31.606
- Boys.

36:31.607 --> 36:32.857
Enough.

36:32.858 --> 36:34.275
- Should have never
gone over there.

36:34.276 --> 36:35.985
- What?

36:35.986 --> 36:38.237
- No, no, Dad,
this was my fault.

36:38.238 --> 36:41.574
If I hadn't fallen asleep,
I would have heard Miss Lang.

36:41.575 --> 36:44.660
- Or if I'd been
listening at all.

36:44.661 --> 36:46.787
I was wrong.

36:46.788 --> 36:49.957
I can't just shut
everything out.

36:49.958 --> 36:52.209
By doing nothing,
it makes things worse.

36:52.210 --> 36:55.421
- What happened tonight
isn't on either of you.

36:55.422 --> 36:59.342
- Until Luthor is back
behind bars, all of us

36:59.343 --> 37:01.303
need to be ready.

37:03.555 --> 37:06.474
- If you need anything,
we'll have a car right outside.

37:06.475 --> 37:09.477
<i>[tense music]</i>

37:09.478 --> 37:16.818
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:21.740 --> 37:23.324
- Are you OK?

37:23.325 --> 37:27.912
- I'm not sure how
to answer that.

37:27.913 --> 37:29.997
- I'm so sorry.

37:29.998 --> 37:32.124
If I hadn't gone after Luthor--

37:32.125 --> 37:36.504
- He'd be building his
headquarters in Smallville.

37:36.505 --> 37:38.506
If something had
happened to you--

37:38.507 --> 37:40.091
- Mom.

37:40.092 --> 37:42.385
Look.

37:42.386 --> 37:47.306
I-- I get it was scary, but you
can't let guys like that win.

37:47.307 --> 37:50.769
They're just gonna bully
you into doing nothing.

37:51.937 --> 37:54.772
- You're right.

37:54.773 --> 37:57.525
You're right.

37:57.526 --> 38:00.861
And not just about Luthor.

38:00.862 --> 38:03.531
I think that you
should go study abroad.

38:03.532 --> 38:05.366
- What?

38:05.367 --> 38:07.326
No.

38:07.327 --> 38:08.744
Luthor's still out there.

38:08.745 --> 38:10.955
- Which is exactly
why you should leave.

38:10.956 --> 38:12.915
- What if something
happens to you?

38:12.916 --> 38:16.711
- No, honey, I'm gonna be fine.

38:16.712 --> 38:20.881
I'm more protected
now than ever.

38:20.882 --> 38:26.679
You've come so far,
and I'm so proud of you.

38:26.680 --> 38:28.723
You deserve this.

38:28.724 --> 38:32.727
You're ready for this.

38:32.728 --> 38:34.228
- Really?

38:34.229 --> 38:37.231
<i>[soft music]</i>

38:37.232 --> 38:41.610
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:41.611 --> 38:43.404
Thank you.

38:43.405 --> 38:50.495
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:55.042 --> 38:56.417
- So you're leaving Smallville?

38:56.418 --> 38:58.127
- Just for junior year.

38:58.128 --> 39:00.796
It's not like I won't
see you guys again.

39:00.797 --> 39:02.590
You'll come visit me, right?

39:02.591 --> 39:04.258
- Totally.

39:04.259 --> 39:06.385
- For sure.

39:06.386 --> 39:07.636
Where are you gonna go?

39:07.637 --> 39:10.264
- I'm thinking Santiago, Chile.

39:10.265 --> 39:12.183
Or maybe somewhere in Greece.

39:12.184 --> 39:14.268
- I mean, do you want
us to help you decide?

39:14.269 --> 39:16.312
- Like what?
You'd fly me to those places?

39:16.313 --> 39:18.355
- You're the one always saying
that I'm wasting my powers.

39:18.356 --> 39:20.107
I can't think of a better
way to use them.

39:20.108 --> 39:24.612
- And I could really use
a day trip to just relax.

39:24.613 --> 39:26.363
- Where should we go first?

39:26.364 --> 39:27.573
- Wait.

39:27.574 --> 39:28.616
Like, what?

39:28.617 --> 39:29.784
Fly out right now?

39:29.785 --> 39:31.452
- Greek islands?
- Greek islands.

39:31.453 --> 39:32.495
- No, no, no.

39:32.496 --> 39:35.290
[screams]

39:39.086 --> 39:40.628
- Is he really gone?

39:40.629 --> 39:44.840
- The boys heard him arriving
in Metropolis last night.

39:44.841 --> 39:47.885
- You think he's moved on?

39:47.886 --> 39:49.678
- I don't think
Lex Luthor is someone

39:49.679 --> 39:52.181
who can ever really move on.

39:52.182 --> 39:53.808
- Lana, about last night--

39:53.809 --> 39:55.476
- No, Clark, please.

39:55.477 --> 39:56.852
Don't apologize.

39:56.853 --> 39:59.356
Just promise me
you'll stop him.

40:01.024 --> 40:02.233
- I promise.

40:02.234 --> 40:04.318
- Good.

40:04.319 --> 40:07.488
What do you think
he's planning next?

40:07.489 --> 40:10.491
<i>[tense music]</i>

40:10.492 --> 40:17.624
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:21.711 --> 40:23.963
- Milton's lights didn't work.

40:23.964 --> 40:26.924
- He was stronger
than I thought.

40:26.925 --> 40:28.175
- You were reckless.

40:28.176 --> 40:30.010
- It won't happen again.
- Lex.

40:30.011 --> 40:33.431
- It won't.
Why are you here?

40:35.934 --> 40:38.979
- Because you
asked me to choose.

40:45.277 --> 40:48.113
And I choose you, Lex.

40:49.573 --> 40:51.657
I'll always choose you.

40:51.658 --> 40:54.660
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

40:54.661 --> 41:01.793
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:02.252 --> 41:04.671
You're doing this wrong.

41:06.173 --> 41:09.092
- It was hard to do on my own.

41:10.302 --> 41:12.971
- I'm not talking
about your eye.

41:15.599 --> 41:17.933
- What are you thinking?

41:17.934 --> 41:21.061
- Well,

41:21.062 --> 41:25.566
the first thing we need to do

41:25.567 --> 41:27.484
is get you a killer suit.

41:27.485 --> 41:29.236
<i>[IDLES'
"When the Lights Come On"]</i>

41:29.237 --> 41:34.366
<i>- ♪ Feels like
I'm coming home ♪</i>

41:34.367 --> 41:40.080
<i>♪ Feels like I'm coming home ♪</i>

41:40.081 --> 41:43.292
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:43.293 --> 41:49.298
<i>♪ A narcissist
on a cucking stool ♪</i>

41:49.299 --> 41:53.636
<i>♪ The kids are not ♪</i>

41:53.637 --> 41:57.682
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:01.228 --> 42:04.146
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

42:04.147 --> 42:11.488
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:21.039 --> 42:23.500
- Greg, move your head.
